{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019yUUVWxJFvKXV8mmuHGDBA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me provide a detailed summary of the web UI code structure.\n\n## Web UI Code Exploration Summary\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche web UI implementation. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. Web Server and Handler Code\n\n**Main Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1336 lines)\n\n**Key Components:**\n- **Handler struct** (lines 68-76): Central server component managing:\n  - `store` (RunStore) - database access\n  - `captures` (CaptureStore) - step execution history\n  - `logStore` (LogStore) - indexed log file lookups\n  - `container` (ContainerLogger) - Docker integration\n  - `logBroadcast` (*logstream.Broadcaster) - SSE streaming\n  - `pages` - cached HTML templates\n  - `mux` (*http.ServeMux) - HTTP routing\n\n**HTTP Routes Defined** (lines 122-139):\n- **HTML Pages:**\n  - `GET /` → handleProjectOverview\n  - `GET /runs` → handleRunsList\n  - `GET /runs/{id}` → handleRunDetail\n  - `GET /projects/{name}` → handleProjectDetail\n  - `GET /projects/{name}/runs` → handleProjectRuns (redirects)\n\n- **JSON APIs:**\n  - `GET /api/runs` → handleAPIRuns\n  - `GET /api/runs/{id}` → handleAPIRunDetail\n  - `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` → handleAPIStepOutput\n  - `POST /api/runs/{id}/stop` → handleAPIStopRun\n  - `DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container` → handleAPIDeleteContainer\n  - `DELETE /api/projects/{name}/containers` → handleAPIDeleteProjectContainers\n  - `GET /api/projects` → handleAPIProjects\n  - `GET /api/projects/{name}/info` → handleAPIProjectInfo\n  - `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` → handleAPIWorkflows\n  - `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` → handleAPIStream (Server-Sent Events)\n\n### 2. HTML Templates Location\n\n**Path:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`\n\n**Files:**\n- **layout.html** (20 lines) - Master layout with navbar and CSS link\n- **runs.html** (116 lines) - Runs list page with project filter dropdown\n- **run_detail.html** (323 lines) - Run details page with steps table, live log viewer, and stream integration\n- **projects.html** (39 lines) - Project overview landing page with health cards\n- **project_detail.html** (272 lines) - Project detail page with info panel, workflow DAG visualization, and step drawer\n\n**Styling:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\n### 3. Runs List Page Implementation\n\n**Handler Function:** `handleRunsList` (lines 229-275)\n\n**Data Structure Passed to Template:**\n```go\n{\n  \"Title\": \"Runs\",\n  \"Runs\": []*domain.Run,\n  \"Projects\": []projectEntry{Dir, Label, ContainerCount},\n  \"ProjectFilter\": string,\n  \"ProjectLabels\": map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n**Template Details (runs.html):**\n- Project filter dropdown (lines 4-13)\n- Table with columns: Run ID, Title, Project, Workflow, Type, State, Started, Completed, Container, Error\n- JavaScript polling (`/api/runs`) every 3 seconds for real-time updates\n- Project filter via query parameter `?project=<dir>`\n\n### 4. Run Details Page Implementation\n\n**Handler Function:** `handleRunDetail` (lines 366-393)\n\n**Data Structure Passed to Template:**\n```go\n{\n  \"Title\": \"Run <id>\",\n  \"Run\": *domain.Run,\n  \"Steps\": []stepEntry,\n  \"Page\": \"detail\",\n  \"ContainerState\": string\n}\n```\n\n**Template Details (run_detail.html):**\n- Run metadata display: title, workflow, type, started/completed times, container ID\n- Container status badge with dynamic controls (lines 18-33)\n- Steps table showing step name, result, started time, duration (lines 41-68)\n- Collapsible step output rows that fetch content via `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n- Live log viewer with SSE stream integration (lines 71-74)\n- Cancel button for active runs\n- JavaScript features:\n  - SSE stream connection to `/api/runs/{id}/stream` (lines 111-125)\n  - Polling for step updates every 2 seconds (lines 134-243)\n  - Accordion toggle for step outputs (lines 295-320)\n  - Container lifecycle controls (stop, delete)\n\n### 5. Run Domain Type and Storage\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (112 lines)\n\n**Run Struct Fields** (lines 31-46):\n- `ID` string\n- `WorkflowName` string\n- `State` (RunState: pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled)\n- `ActiveSteps` []string\n- `StepExecutions` []*StepExecution\n- `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt` time.Time\n- `ProjectDir` string\n- `ErrorMessage` string\n- `ContainerID` string\n- `BaseSHA` string (Git HEAD for result branch)\n- `ContainerKept` bool\n- `Title` string (one-line summary)\n- `IsHost` bool (host vs container run)\n\n**Parent/Child Relationships:** No parent/child fields exist in the current domain. Runs are independent entities related only through their ProjectDir and WorkflowName.\n\n### 6. Database Schema\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (lines 46-129)\n\n**Runs Table Columns:**\n- id (TEXT PRIMARY KEY)\n- workflow_name (TEXT)\n- state (TEXT)\n- active_steps (TEXT - comma-separated)\n- started_at, completed_at (TEXT)\n- project_dir (TEXT)\n- error_message (TEXT)\n- container_id (TEXT)\n- base_sha (TEXT)\n- container_kept (INTEGER)\n- title (TEXT)\n- is_host (INTEGER)\n\n**Step Executions Table:**\n- id (INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT)\n- run_id (FOREIGN KEY)\n- step_name (TEXT)\n- result (TEXT)\n- started_at, completed_at (TEXT)\n- logs, git_ref (TEXT)\n\n**Supporting Tables:**\n- log_files (run_id, step_name, file_type, file_path, file_size)\n- merge_queue (run_id, branch, project, status)\n- evolution_log (id, project_dir, workflow_name, trigger_run_id)\n\n### 7. Key Handlers and Features\n\n**API Response Types:**\n- `apiRun` (lines 397-409) - JSON run summary\n- `apiRunDetail` (lines 419-423) - Run with steps\n- `apiStep` (lines 411-417) - Step execution data\n\n**Special Features:**\n- **Log Streaming** (lines 782-845): SSE stream from `/api/runs/{id}/stream` for live logs\n- **Container Management**: Stop and delete container operations\n- **Step Output Fetching** (lines 557-632): Tries log index first, then file-based lookup\n- **Project Labels** (lines 1305-1329): Smart labeling system that disambiguates duplicate project names\n- **Workflow Visualization** (project_detail.html): DAG rendering with SVG\n\n### 8. Template Function Map\n\nCustom template functions available to all templates (lines 80-87):\n- `stateColor` - Maps RunState to CSS class\n- `healthColor` - Maps HealthStatus to CSS class\n- `formatTime` - Formats timestamps\n- `formatDuration` - Calculates and formats time differences\n- `truncate` - Truncates strings with ellipsis\n- `shortContainerID` - Shortens Docker container IDs to 12 chars\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** The web UI is a modern HTML/JavaScript application served by the daemon. It uses HTML templates embedded in the binary, polls JSON APIs for updates, uses SSE for real-time logs, and provides full visibility into run execution with step-by-step output inspection and container lifecycle management. There are currently no parent/child run relationships implemented."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af5190c1114abf48d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63590\ntool_uses: 26\nduration_ms: 46705</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"daab45ac-603f-4f11-b864-beeca03c969d","uuid":"447a9774-667c-4960-b7a8-69a2d98d4d04","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the web UI code in this project. I need to understand:\n1. Where the web server/handler code lives\n2. How the runs list page and run details page are implemented (templates, handlers)\n3. How runs are stored and what fields they have (especially parent/child relationships)\n4. The existing HTML templates for runs\n\nSearch thoroughly in internal/adapters/, cmd/, and any web-related directories. Look for HTML templates, handler files, and