{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GTiNfz8gCtwhdkyrRkEmzh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Here's my plan:\n\n1. **Domain**: Add `ParentRunID` to `domain.Run`\n2. **Proto**: Add `parent_run_id` to `RunWorkflowRequest` and regenerate (or just add the field manually to the Go struct since modifying proto generation might be complex)\n3. **SQLite**: Add migration for `parent_run_id` column, update `runSelectCols`, `scanRun`, `CreateRun`, `UpdateRun`\n4. **SQLite**: Add `ListChildRuns` method\n5. **Host executor**: When dispatching child runs, set the parent run ID on the created run (need to pass it through the gRPC request or set it after creation)\n\n\n6. **Web handler**: Update `handleRunDetail` to fetch parent and child runs, and update `handleRunsList` to group runs by parent/child relationships\n7. **API**: Include `parent_run_id` in the `apiRun` response\n8. **Templates**: Update the run detail and runs list templates to display the hierarchy\n9. **Tests**: Add coverage for the new functionality\n\nFor setting the parent run ID, the cleanest approach is to add the `parent_run_id` field to the proto request, then pass the host run ID as the parent when executing child workflows.\n\nActually, modifying the proto and regenerating might be complex with protoc dependencies. A simpler alternative: after the dispatcher creates the child run, I can fetch it from the store and set its `ParentRunID` directly to the host run ID.\n\nFetching the child run after dispatch...\n\nBut wait, the Executor doesn't have access to its own run ID, so I can't set the parent relationship. The cleanest solution is still to add `ParentRunID` to the proto request and regenerate, though that depends on protoc being available.\n\nLet me take a different approach instead: add the `ParentRunID` field directly to the domain model and database layer, then have the host executor set it after dispatching the child run. I'll also need a method to query child runs by parent ID, which I can add to the store interface. set ParentRunID after dispatching child runs, then update the runner to pass the host run ID to the Executor, modify the web handler to display parent links and child runs in the detail view, add tree grouping to the runs list template, and write tests to cover the new functionality.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1831,"cache_read_input_tokens":46046,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1831},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"daab45ac-603f-4f11-b864-beeca03c969d","uuid":"fcad04de-0812-4a54-8309-00127766a535"}
