{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01N354FfrRomx9fCUbdGdmKm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**Domain & Storage:**\n- Added `ParentRunID` field to `domain.Run`\n- Added `parent_run_id` column to SQLite migration, CreateRun, UpdateRun, scanRun\n- Added `ListChildRuns()` method to `RunStore` interface and SQLite implementation\n\n**Parent-child linking:**\n- Added `HostRunID` field to `host.Executor`\n- After dispatching a child workflow run, the executor sets `ParentRunID` on the child run\n- `host.Runner` passes the orchestrator run ID to the executor\n\n**Web UI - Run Detail page:**\n- Breadcrumb shows parent run link: `Runs / parent-id / child-id`\n- Metadata section shows \"Parent Run\" with link and state badge\n- \"Child Runs\" table section lists all child runs with links, titles, workflow, state, and times\n\n**Web UI - Runs List page:**\n- Parent rows styled with `run-parent-row` class (de-emphasized with opacity)\n- Child rows styled with `run-child-row` class (indented with tree connector `└`)\n- JavaScript polling groups runs so children appear directly after their parent\n\n**API:**\n- `apiRun` includes `parent_run_id` field\n- `apiRunDetail` includes `child_runs` array\n\n**Tests:**\n- SQLite: `TestRunParentRunID` (CRUD, ListChildRuns) and backward compat test\n- Web handler: parent/child links in detail page, no parent/child for standalone runs, API detail with child runs, API list with parent_run_id, tree grouping CSS classes\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":334,"cache_read_input_tokens":96032,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":334},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"daab45ac-603f-4f11-b864-beec